132    //

959    /**
960    * <p>This method uses reflection to build a suitable
961    * <code>toString</code> value which includes static fields.</p>
962    *
963    * <p>It uses <code>AccessibleObject.setAccessible</code> to gain access to private
964    * fields. This means that it will throw a security exception if run
965    * under a security manager, if the permissions are not set up correctly.
966    * It is also not as efficient as testing explicitly. </p>
967    *
968    * <p>Transient fields are not output.</p>
969    *
970    * <p>Superclass fields will be appended up to and including the specified superclass.
971    * A null superclass is treated as <code>java.lang.Object</code>.</p>
972    *
973    * <p>If the style is <code>null</code>, the default
974    * <code>ToStringStyle</code> is used.</p>
975    *
976    * @param <T> the type of the output object
977    * @param object the Object to be output
978    * @param style the style of the <code>toString</code> to create,
979    * may be <code>null</code>
980    * @param reflectUpToClass the superclass to reflect up to (inclusive),
981    * may be <code>null</code>
982    * @return the String result
983    * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the Object is <code>null</code>
984    */
